'''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine''' ({{ill|Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|ja|洲崎濱宮神明神社|12=draft}}, ''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Jinja'') is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in the [[Shiobama District]], [[Yokkaichi]], [[Mie Prefecture]], Japan. It is often collectively referred to as "Miyamado Shrine" due to the large presence of its {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
[[File:Miyamado-inari(Mie).JPG|thumb|Miyamado Inari Shrine]]
The shrine's name "濱" (''Hama'') is also written as "浜" or "濵."

The subordinate shrine, known as '''Miyamado Inari Shrine''' ({{ill|Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja|海山道稲荷神社|12=draft}}), is larger than the main Shinmei Shrine and is famous for the "Fox Wedding Ceremony" ({{ill|Kitsune no yomeiri|lt=Fox Wedding|ja|狐の嫁入り|12=draft}}). 

The grounds also include multiple Inari shrines, {{ill|Tenjinja|lt=Tenjin shrines|ja|天神社|12=draft}}, and unique features such as Japan’s largest statue of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|12=draft}}.

== Enshrined Deities ==
=== Shinmei Shrine ===
{{Div col}}
* {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|lt=Amenokoyane-no-Mikoto|ja|天児屋根命|1=Ame-no-Koyane|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Takemikazuchi|lt=Takemikazuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|建御雷命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt-Ukanomitama-no-Kami|ja|倉稲魂命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Oyamakui no Kami|lt=Ōyamakui-no-Kami|ja|大山祇神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kagu-tsuchi|lt=Kagutsuchi-no-Kami|ja|火之迦具土神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kagu-tsuchi|lt=Ho-musubi-no-Kami|ja|火産霊神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ukemochi|lt=Ukemochi-no-Kami|ja|保食神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Yamatohime-no-mikoto|lt=Yamatohime-no-Mikoto|ja|倭姫命|1=Yamatohime-no-mikoto|12=draft}}
{{Div col end}}

=== Inari Shrine ===
* {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Kami|ja|倉稲魂命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Kami|ja|大己貴命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ōta-no-Kami|ja|大田命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ukemochi|lt=Ukemochi-no-Kami|ja|保食神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōmiyanome-no-Kami|ja|大宮能売神|12=draft}}

== History ==
The shrine is traditionally said to have been founded in [[876]] (the 18th year of the {{ill|Jōgan era|ja|貞観|12=draft}}). During the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft}}, the area was coastal and formed a sandbar called "Suzaki." Thus, the shrine became known as "Hama-no-Miya" (Shrine of the Beach).

The exact date of the establishment of the {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft}} is unknown.

== Shrine Buildings and Grounds ==
The grounds include the {{ill|Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja|海山道稲荷神社|12=draft}}, which surpasses the Shinmei Shrine in scale.

There are over 20 subsidiary {{ill|Inari shrines|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft}}, a {{ill|Tenjin shrine|ja|天神社|12=draft}} housing Japan’s largest statue of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|12=draft}}, and various monuments such as the Pen Mound, Eyeglass Mound, and Fox Mound.

== Festivals and Events ==
* festival: October 3–5
* Inari Grand Festival: April 8–9
* Fox Wedding Ceremony: Held on {{ill|Setsubun|ja|節分|12=draft}} (February), this purification ritual involves a mock wedding procession. Participants representing the bride and groom wear fox masks, and a "bean-throwing" event is also held.

== location ==
1-62 Miyamado Town, [[Yokkaichi]], [[Mie Prefecture]], Japan

== Access ==
* A short walk from [[Kintetsu Nagoya Line]]'s [[Miyamado Station]].
