'''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine''' ({{ill|Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|ja|洲崎濱宮神明神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|qq=}}, ''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Jinja'') is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in the [[Shiobama District]], [[Yokkaichi]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], Japan. It is often collectively referred to as "Miyamado Shrine" due to the large presence of its [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari Shrine]].
== Overview == [[File:Miyamado-inari(Mie).JPG|thumb|Miyamado Inari Shrine]] The shrine's name "濱" (''Hama'') is also written as "浜" or "濵."
The subordinate shrine, known as '''Miyamado Inari Shrine''' ({{ill|Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja|海山道稲荷神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyamado Inari Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 洲崎濱宮神明神社}}), is larger than the main Shinmei Shrine and is famous for the "Fox Wedding Ceremony" ([[:en:Kitsune no yomeiri|Fox Wedding]]).
The grounds also include multiple Inari shrines, {{ill|Tenjinja|lt=Tenjin shrines|ja|天神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenjinja|qq=}}, and unique features such as Japan’s largest statue of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
== Enshrined Deities == === Shinmei Shrine === {{Div col}} * {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|lt=Amenokoyane-no-Mikoto|ja|天児屋根命|1=Ame-no-Koyane|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Koyane|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Koyane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天児屋命}} * [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]] * {{ill|Takemikazuchi|lt=Takemikazuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|建御雷命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemikazuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to タケミカヅチ}} * [[:en:Emperor Nintoku|Emperor Nintoku]] * {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スサノオ}} * {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt-Ukanomitama-no-Kami|ja|倉稲魂命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ウカノミタマ}} * {{ill|Oyamakui no Kami|lt=Ōyamakui-no-Kami|ja|大山祇神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oyamakui no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオヤマツミ}} * {{ill|Kagu-tsuchi|lt=Kagutsuchi-no-Kami|ja|火之迦具土神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagu-tsuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to カグツチ}} * {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * {{ill|Kagu-tsuchi|lt=Ho-musubi-no-Kami|ja|火産霊神|1=Kagu-tsuchi|lt=Kagutsuchi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagu-tsuchi|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagutsuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to カグツチ}} * [[:en:Ukemochi|Ukemochi-no-Kami]] * [[:en:Yamatohime-no-mikoto|Yamatohime-no-Mikoto]] {{Div col end}}
=== Inari Shrine === * {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Kami|ja|倉稲魂命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ウカノミタマ}} * {{ill|Ōkuninushi|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Kami|ja|大己貴命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大国主}} * {{ill|Ōta-no-Kami|ja|大田命|1=Ōta-no-Mikoto|2=ja|3=太田命|4=fr|5=大田命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōta-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōta-no-Mikoto|qq=}} * [[:en:Ukemochi|Ukemochi-no-Kami]] * {{ill|Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōmiyanome-no-Kami|ja|大宮能売神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオミヤノメ}}
== History == The shrine is traditionally said to have been founded in [[:en:876|876]] (the 18th year of the [[:en:Zhenguan|Jōgan era]]). During the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], the area was coastal and formed a sandbar called "Suzaki." Thus, the shrine became known as "Hama-no-Miya" (Shrine of the Beach).
The exact date of the establishment of the [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari Shrine]] is unknown.
== Shrine Buildings and Grounds == The grounds include the {{ill|Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja|海山道稲荷神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyamado Inari Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 洲崎濱宮神明神社}}, which surpasses the Shinmei Shrine in scale.
There are over 20 subsidiary [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari shrines]], a {{ill|Tenjin shrine|ja|天神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenjin shrine|qq=}} housing Japan’s largest statue of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and various monuments such as the Pen Mound, Eyeglass Mound, and Fox Mound.
== Festivals and Events == * festival: October 3–5 * Inari Grand Festival: April 8–9 * Fox Wedding Ceremony: Held on [[:en:Setsubun|Setsubun]] (February), this purification ritual involves a mock wedding procession. Participants representing the bride and groom wear fox masks, and a "bean-throwing" event is also held.
== location == 1-62 Miyamado Town, [[Yokkaichi]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], Japan
== Access == * A short walk from [[:en:Kintetsu Nagoya Line|Kintetsu Nagoya Line]]'s [[:en:Miyamado Station|Miyamado Station]].
== See Also == {{Commonscat|Miyamado-jinja|Miyamado Shrine}} * [[:en:Shinmei shrines|Shinmei Shrine]] * [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari Shrine]]
