'''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine''' ({{ill|Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|ja|洲崎濱宮神明神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|qq=}}, ''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Jinja'') is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in the [[Shiobama District]], [[:en:Yokkaichi|Yokkaichi]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], Japan. It is often collectively referred to as "Miyamado Shrine" due to the large presence of its [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari Shrine]].
== Overview == [[File:Miyamado-inari(Mie).JPG|thumb|Miyamado Inari Shrine]] The shrine's name "濱" (''Hama'') is also written as "浜" or "濵."
The subordinate shrine, known as '''Miyamado Inari Shrine''' ({{ill|Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja|海山道稲荷神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyamado Inari Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 洲崎濱宮神明神社}}), is larger than the main Shinmei Shrine and is famous for the "Fox Wedding Ceremony" ([[:en:Kitsune no yomeiri|Fox Wedding]]).
The grounds also include multiple Inari shrines, {{ill|Tenjinja|lt=Tenjin shrines|ja|天神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenjinja|qq=}}, and unique features such as Japan’s largest statue of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
