'''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine''' ({{ill|Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|ja|洲崎濱宮神明神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Shrine|1=Miyamado Inari Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11556511}}, ''Suzaki Hamamiya Shinmei Jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|qid=Q845945|lt=Shinto shrine|1=Shinto shrine}} located in the [[Shiobama District]], {{ill|Yokkaichi|en|Yokkaichi|qid=Q26410|lt=Yokkaichi|1=Yokkaichi}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|en|Mie Prefecture|qid=Q128196|lt=Mie Prefecture|1=Mie Prefecture}}, Japan. It is often collectively referred to as "Miyamado Shrine" due to the large presence of its {{ill|Inari shrine|en|Inari shrine|qid=Q514480|lt=Inari Shrine|1=Inari shrine}}.

== Overview ==
[[File:Miyamado-inari(Mie).JPG|thumb|Miyamado Inari Shrine]]
The shrine's name "濱" (''Hama'') is also written as "浜" or "濵."

The subordinate shrine, known as '''Miyamado Inari Shrine''' ({{ill|Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja|海山道稲荷神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyamado Inari Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 洲崎濱宮神明神社}}), is larger than the main Shinmei Shrine and is famous for the "Fox Wedding Ceremony" ({{ill|Kitsune no yomeiri|en|Kitsune no yomeiri|qid=Q11571371|lt=Fox Wedding|1=Kitsune no yomeiri}}). 

The grounds also include multiple Inari shrines, {{ill|Tenjinsha|lt=Tenjin shrines|ja|天神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenjinsha|qq=}}, and unique features such as Japan’s largest statue of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|1=Sugawara no Michizane|2=ja|3=菅原道真|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|1=Sugawara no Michizane|2=ja|3=菅原道真|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q382005}}.

